.TH "rc_validate_filter" 9 "rc_validate_filter" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rc_validate_filter \- checks that the scancode and mask are valid and provides sensible defaults
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rc_validate_filter
.BI "(struct rc_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "struct rc_scancode_filter *filter "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the struct rc_dev descriptor of the device
.IP "filter" 12
the scancode and mask
.SH "RETURN"
0 or -EINVAL if the filter is not valid
